rrspacing(x) returns the reciprocal of the relative spacing near x.
It is roughly abs(fraction(x)) * radix(x)**digits(x).

default real examples:
x = -10  rrspacing(x) = 1.048576e+07
x = -1  rrspacing(x) = 8388608
x = -0.5  rrspacing(x) = 8388608
x = 0  rrspacing(x) = 0
x = 0.5  rrspacing(x) = 8388608
x = 1  rrspacing(x) = 8388608
x = 10  rrspacing(x) = 1.048576e+07

kind examples:
rrspacing(1.0)   = 8388608
rrspacing(1.0_4) = 8388608
rrspacing(1.0_8) = 4.5035996273705e+15

nearby-value examples:
rrspacing(1.0)              = 8388608
rrspacing(nearest(1.0,1.0)) = 8388609
rrspacing(2.0)              = 8388608
